'''Finse''' is a locality in [[Wikipedia:Norway|Norway]], with its railway station located alongside the main line between Oslo and Bergen. At a height of 1,222 meters, it is the highest station in the entire Norwegian railway system.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.bbc.com/travel/article/20130712-the-perfect-trip-norway|title=The perfect trip: Norway|publisher=BBC Travel|author=Christa Larwood|language=English|date=2013-09-04|archivedate=20231002194036}}</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.bbc.com/travel/article/20230130-the-highest-rail-route-in-northern-europe|title=The highest rail route in northern Europe|publisher=BBC Travel|author=Anthony Ham|language=English|date=2023-01-31|archivedate=20230315034857}}</ref>

Filming for [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']] took place in Finse in [[1979]] to represent [[Echo Base]] on the [[planet]] [[Hoth]].

